# 📊 Unemployment Analysis in India using Python

## Project Overview

This project was developed as part of the **CodeAlpha Data Science Internship**. The objective was to analyze unemployment trends in India, evaluate the impact of the Covid-19 pandemic on employment, identify regional and seasonal patterns, and derive meaningful insights through data analysis and visualization.

## Key Objectives

* Perform data cleaning and preprocessing.
* Analyze unemployment trends across different regions of India.
* Investigate the impact of Covid-19 on unemployment rates.
* Compare Urban and Rural unemployment patterns.
* Identify seasonal trends and regional disparities.
* Develop interactive visualizations and dashboards.
* Generate policy-oriented insights and recommendations.

## Tools & Technologies

* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Matplotlib
* Seaborn
* Plotly
* Scikit-Learn
* YData Profiling
* Google Colab

## Analysis Performed

* Data Cleaning and Preprocessing
* Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
* State-wise Unemployment Analysis
* Covid-19 Impact Assessment
* Urban vs Rural Comparison
* Correlation Analysis
* Seasonal Trend Analysis
* Interactive Dashboard Visualization
* Unemployment Trend Forecasting

## Key Findings

* Unemployment rates increased significantly during the Covid-19 period.
* Urban regions experienced greater employment disruptions compared to rural regions.
* Several states consistently reported higher unemployment rates than the national average.
* Seasonal fluctuations indicate variations in labor demand throughout the year.
* Labour participation rate showed a measurable relationship with unemployment levels.

## Outcome

The project provides a comprehensive understanding of unemployment patterns in India and demonstrates the application of data science techniques for economic analysis, trend identification, and evidence-based decision making.

